LOCATION> States </LOCATION> to increase access to its market to reduce a $ 10 billion trade imbalance it registered last year. When asked what they most closely associated with their Asian neighbor, a majority of the 2,292 Japanese respondents cited the upcoming Olympic Games. But 30 percent of the <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Koreans </LOCATION> said they associate <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> with its colonization of the Korean peninusula from 1910 to 1945. About 48 percent of the <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Koreans </LOCATION> also said relations with <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> were negative, up 11 percentage points, and only 24 percent said relations with <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> were positive.
