<HEAD>Book Checked Out By Missing Newlywed Found in Minnesota</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: CORRECTS typo in police commander's last name, DiVito, in 5th
graf, `Commander Ettore ....'</NOTE>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A hint that a missing couple from <ORGANIZATION> Wheaton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> College </ORGANIZATION> are still alive has come from an unlikely source _ a vacation book on <LOCATION> Hawaii </LOCATION> checked out of a suburban <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> library and found in <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION>. The book was returned to the <ORGANIZATION> Wheaton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Library </ORGANIZATION> from a <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Paul </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Minn. </LOCATION>, post office where it was found. It had been checked out with <PERSON> Scott </PERSON> <PERSON> Swanson </PERSON>'s library card, police said Wednesday. <PERSON> Swanson </PERSON>, 23, and <PERSON> Carolyn </PERSON> <PERSON> MacLean </PERSON>, 21, have not been seen since April 2. Their luxury car was found in a downtown <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> alley with most of their belongings undisturbed and the keys still in the ignition. Police initially suspected the couple had met with foul play. But some of the circumstances surrounding their disappearance _ they were married secretly about a week earlier _ led to speculation they may have eloped. Commander <PERSON> Ettore </PERSON> <PERSON> DiVito </PERSON>, who is heading the investigation, said the book, `` Hidden <LOCATION> Hawaii </LOCATION>: The Adventurer's Guide'' was checked out of the <LOCATION> Wheaton </LOCATION> library on March 29 and was found Saturday in <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Paul </LOCATION>. Although <PERSON> DiVito </PERSON> decline to chacterize the find as a `` breakthrough'' in the investigation, when he was asked whether police believed the couple may have been in <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Paul </LOCATION> and headed for <LOCATION> Hawaii </LOCATION>, he replied: ` It's a possibility. We're checking out both possibilities. `` We're sending flyers to <PERSON> St. </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON>, to the missing pers