areas'' available for leasing and `` might leave us without a sale,'' as happened once before when no one bid on areas left out of a previous prohibition. The <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> postponement involved 14 million acres in the eastern <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> north of the <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Keys </LOCATION> up to about <LOCATION> Naples </LOCATION>. The area will be dropped from a scheduled offering of tracts in the eastern gulf scheduled for November and will be offered separately. The department announced no schedule for that second offering. The governor's office in <LOCATION> Tallahassee </LOCATION> said under today's agreement it could not occur before next May In the meantime, two 14-member federal-state committees will study oil spills and cleanup in the gulf. The subcommittee measure would forbid drilling in a slightly larger area, about 16 million acres. It was the second deletion of substantial acreage off <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> in an attempt to satisfy the state. <PERSON> Hodel </PERSON> ruled the areas around the keys off limits in March. The subcommittee proposal also called for delaying the northern <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> offering until October, in effect putting <PERSON> Hodel </PERSON>'s delay into law.
