<HEAD>Bus Wrecks, 16 Burned to Death</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS throughout to UPDATE with 16 killed, police holding
driver. No pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A bus blew a tire, hit a wall and burst into flames today, burning 16 people to death in the southern state of <LOCATION> Andhra </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pradesh </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trust </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> India </ORGANIZATION> reported. Among the victims were seven children. The news agency said the bus, carrying 38 people, wrecked on the outskirts of the state capital at <LOCATION> Hyderabad </LOCATION>. It said two people were being treated for serious burn injuries at a local hospital and 10 others escaped with minor injuries. The driver and the cleaner of the bus, who survived the accident, have surrendered to the police, <ORGANIZATION> PTI </ORGANIZATION> said. Officials earlier had reported a death toll of 27 but later corrected it to 16.
