<HEAD>Attorney: Asner To Pay Child Support</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Actor <PERSON> Ed </PERSON> <PERSON> Asner </PERSON> will pay more than $ 2,100 monthly to the mother of a 10-month-old child he fathered out of wedlock, a lawyer said Thursday. Under the agreement, <PERSON> Asner </PERSON> must pay $ 2,000 for expenses and $ 100 for medical insurance each month to support <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Vogelman </PERSON>, said attorney <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> Supancic </PERSON>, who represents the former husband of the child's mother. The actor, who admitted paternity, must also pay the mortgage on a $ 300,000 condominium where the child lives with his mother <PERSON> Carol </PERSON> <PERSON> Jean </PERSON> <PERSON> Vogelman </PERSON>, <PERSON> Supancic </PERSON> said. The agreement ends seven months of medical tests and testimony. <PERSON> Asner </PERSON>, star of television's `` Bronx Zoo'' and the old `` <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Tyler </PERSON> <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> Show'' and `` <PERSON> Lou </PERSON> <PERSON> Grant </PERSON>,'' eventually conceded the child was his. The actor became involved in the court action when Ms. <PERSON> Vogelman </PERSON>'s ex-husband, <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Stone </PERSON>, alleged his $ 3,000-a-month alimony payment was being used to support a child that was n't his. Under the court-supervised agreement, <PERSON> Stone </PERSON> must pay $ 2,000 monthly to Ms. <PERSON> Vogelman </PERSON> for the next three months, $ 1,500 monthly for the following 10 months and $ 1,000 monthly thereafter. `` We thought it was a little out of balance that <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Stone </PERSON> was paying such a high monthly sum when a man of Mr. <PERSON> Asner </PERSON>'s stature had become involved with Ms. <PERSON> Vogelman </PERSON> and they had conceived a child together,'' <PERSON> Supancic </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Asner </PERSON> attorney <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Schiff </PERSON> said only that <PERSON> Asner </PERSON> and Ms