that affects the lives of others,'' he said. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> told his audience that while the government could not require drug-testing or drug-education programs of private businesses, `` each of you, pesonally, can stand up against drug use.'' <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said he fully supports the zero-tolerance policy under which yachts and other vehicles on which drugs have been found have been seized. `` I do n't mind inconveniencing a yacht owner or a car driver if it results somehow in saving the life of one kid,'' <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said. In his talk with reporters on <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Two </ORGANIZATION>, on the way home to <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> from <LOCATION> Richmond </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said, `` I just ca n't get too excited about the yacht owner, even though some would like you to believe I am one.'' `` Mine is 28 feet long. I want that in there too,'' he said, referring to the $ 40,000 racing powerboat that he keeps at his vacation retreat in <LOCATION> Kennebunkport </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Maine </LOCATION>.
