s and subjective approaches, but ... we have every right to expect similar self-criticism, responsibility and reason from other states, too.'' The <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION>, he said, should become `` a unique center for harmonizing actions of states in our interdependent world.'' <PERSON> Petrovsky </PERSON> said all nations should disclose to the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION> information on their troops abroad and their foreign military bases. But, asked if the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> would make the first step and disclose its military information, <PERSON> Petrovsky </PERSON> said: `` This is not a one-actor theater, but the world stage. We are ready to participate in the exchange of data if other countries, the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and <ORGANIZATION> NATO </ORGANIZATION>, do the same.'' In its month-long session on disarmament, the <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assembly </ORGANIZATION> is expected to adopt resolutions and a final document setting out a realistic agenda for disarmament and arms control. Western diplomats have indicated that if the documents are unacceptable, there will be no consensus and there could be divisive votes. The Soviet proposals include: _ Creation of a <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> naval force aimed at maintaning freedom of navigation, and holding a joint trial exercise with fleets of the permanent members of the <ORGANIZATION> Security </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> _ the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> _ U.N supervision of troop withdrawal from foreign territories and the expansion of <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> peacekeeping forces. The <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> has proposed elimination of foreign military presence and military bases in foreign territories by the year 2,000. _ Creation of an international monitoring and verification agency, covering both disarmament and political settlement of conflicts and crises _ Creation of a world space organization under <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> auspices to ensure safeguards in making outer space strictly for peaceful purposes The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> regards many of the proposals as infringements upon its ability to behave unilaterally in its own interests and pursue, for example, its space-based anti-missile defense initiative, known as `` Star Wars.''
