<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Prime Minister <PERSON> Noboru </PERSON> <PERSON> Takeshita </PERSON> said <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> has gained the status of an economic power, and it is his responsibility to assert that role at next week's economic summit in <LOCATION> Toronto </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Takeshita </PERSON> said Wednesday his goals at the summit are to discuss cooperation on trade, resolving the problems of international debt and restoring self-sustained growth to developing countries.
