<SECOND>PM-Allegheny International,0333</SECOND>
<HEAD>Way Cleared For Reorganization Plan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A federal appeals court has given <ORGANIZATION> Allegheny </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> approval to file a bankruptcy reorganization plan. The <ORGANIZATION> 3rd </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Circuit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Appeals </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION> also said that management may count votes cast at a shareholders meeting next week and announce the results immediately. The court, which handed down its ruling Tuesday, previously had said the appliance maker could do none of those things without court permission. <ORGANIZATION> Allegheny </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Romanoff </PERSON> said management plans to file a reorganization plan by the end of the month, but he declined to specify whether the filing would precede a shareholders' meeting June 20, when votes are to be cast for board seats. `` The sooner the company emerges from Chapter 11, the stronger it will be,'' Chairman <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Travers </PERSON> said Wednesday. Under Chapter 11 of federal bankruptcy laws, a company is protected from its creditors while it reorganizes. Management and a shareholders group, led by the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> investment firm Spear, <ORGANIZATION> Leeds </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Kellogg </PERSON>, are fueding over how to allocate the company's resources in satisfying its obligations. The dissident shareholders group is also challenging management for control of the board. Seven seats, a majority, are open. <PERSON> Irwin </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Jacobs </PERSON>, the company's largest shareholder, said Wednesday that he is siding with the investment banking company in its bid to take control of the board. The previously uncommitted <PERSON> Jacobs </PERSON> heads an investor group that owns 9 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Allegheny </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION>'s 10.8 million common shares. Separately, <PERSON> Victor </PERSON> <PERSON> Kiam </PERSON>, chairman of <ORGANIZATION> Remington </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Products </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, said Wednesday he told Spear, <ORGANIZATION> Leeds </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Kellogg </PERSON> he would be interested in helping them form a reorganization plan for <ORGANIZATION> Allegheny </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Kiam </PERSON>, who has been involved in reorganizations of several consumer products companies, said he would meet with <ORGANIZATION> Allegheny </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION>'s management if invited, said <PERSON> Remington </PERSON> spokesman <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Cavior </PERSON>. <ORGANIZATION> Allegheny </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> owns <ORGANIZATION> Sunbeam </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Oster </PERSON> and other appliance and leisure products companies.
