<HEAD>Bond Prices Plunge</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By VIVIAN MARINO</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Interest rates headed higher as bonds plunged in value in early trading today, reflecting widespread concerns about possible hikes in rates overseas, a weak dollar and inflation. Long-term issues took the biggest hit. The yield on the <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION>'s closely watched 30-year bond jumped to 8.94 percent from 8.83 percent late Wednesday, while it fell 1 \ point in price, or $ 12.50 per $ 1,000 in face amount Prices of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> securities started out lower overseas and that carried over into domestic trading following an unconfirmed report from a West German newspaper indicating that country's central bank might be tightening monetary policy. The report said the <ORGANIZATION> Bundesbank </ORGANIZATION> would raise its securities repurchase rate, a key interest rate, one-quarter percentage point to 3.5 percent. `` It is possible,'' said <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Brusca </PERSON>, chief economist for <ORGANIZATION> Nikko </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. International in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> He noted that a high-ranking <ORGANIZATION> Bundesbank </ORGANIZATION> official recently indicated that his country was concerned about inflation due to better-than-expected economic growth in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> and a rise in money supply. At the same time, the West German mark has been weak against the dollar in foreign exchange, and the <ORGANIZATION> Bundesbank </ORGANIZATION> has intervened on several occasions by selling dollars to buy marks. Tightening credit through a hike in interest rates would keep West German inflation in check and also support the mark, <PERSON> Brusca </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Carol </PERSON> <PERSON> Stone </PERSON>, a senior economist at <ORGANIZATION> Nomura </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, said <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> bond traders were concerned that <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> might also be tightening policies, especially as its economy continues to grow, and that could carry over to the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. Adding a negative tone to the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> markets today was a decline in the dollar in foreign exchange and another rise in commodity prices, both of which heighten concerns about inflation, Ms. <PERSON> Stone </PERSON> said. Inflation erodes the value of fixed-income securities, such as bonds and notes. By midday today in the secondary market for <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> bonds, prices of short-term government issues fell between \ point and -RRB- point, intermediate maturities ranged from -LCB- point to -RCB- point lower and long-term issues declined between 1 3-16 point and 1 \ point, according to figures provided by <ORGANIZATION> Telerate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a business-information service The movement of a point is equivalent to a change of $ 10 in the price of a bond with a $ 1,000 face value. The <ORGANIZATION> Merrill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lynch </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Daily </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Index </ORGANIZATION>, which measures price movements on all outstanding <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> issues with maturities of a year or longer, fell 0.65 to 110.03. The <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Daily </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> Bond Index, which makes a similar measurement, stood at 1,152.22, down 6.71. In corporate trading, industrials and utilities fell nearly a point in light trading, according to the investment firm of <ORGANIZATION> Salomon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broth