<HEAD>Corn, Soybeans Close Higher While Wheat Declines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Futures prices of corn, oats and soybeans closed sharply higher Thursday on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION> while wheat futures plunged on fears of a reduction in export sales. The three corn contracts for 1988 delivery advanced the limit for daily trading for the third consecutive session as dry conditions prevailed in the parched Corn Belt. <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION> expanded its daily price limit for corn from 10 to 15 cents a bushel Thursday following two days of 10-cent advances. But profit-taking limited the gains in soybean prices, analysts said. `` I think this demonstrates the more serious concern about potential damage to corn than to the other crops,'' said <PERSON> Dale </PERSON> <PERSON> Gustafson </PERSON>, an analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Burnham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lambert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc </ORGANIZATION>. The sell-off in wheat futures was prompted by <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Trade Representative <PERSON> Clayton </PERSON> <PERSON> Yeutter </PERSON>'s statement early Thursday that export subsidy programs may be reviewed if the drought continues, analysts said. Traders sold wheat futures heavily despite <ORGANIZATION> Agriculture </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Lyng </PERSON>'s denial of any plans to reduce subsidized exports. At the close, wheat was 8 -LCB- cents to 16 cents lower with the contract for delivery in July at $ 3.78 a bushel; corn was 6 -LCB- cents to 15 cents higher with July at $ 2.94 -LCB- a bushel; oats were 4 -LCB- cents to 10 cents higher with July at $ 2.89 a bushel; soybeans were 6 -LCB- cents lower to 22 cents higher with July at $ 9.42 a bushel.
