<HEAD>Auto Production Declines This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce 254,541 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's 255,289, <PERSON> Ward </PERSON>'s Automotive Reports said Thursday This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago, in which 229,382 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal said. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> automakers were scheduled to make 167,791 cars this week, compared with 170,279 a week ago and 152,751 in the same week in 1987. Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 86,750, compared with last week's 84,910 and last year's 76,631. Canadian automakers were to build 24,646 cars this week, down from 27,198 a week ago and up from last year's 18,315. Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 20,920, compared with 20,461 a week ago and 18,507 in the same week last year.
